15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 2232, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 2232. The Commission, through the Oklahoma Tourism and
19 Recreation Department, may sponsor, promote, and implement an annual
20 statewide tourism and recreation industry conference to promote the
21 tourism and recreation industry. The Department is authorized to
22 may partner with private entities for the administration and
23 execution of the conference. The Department may enter into
24 contracts or agreements pursuant to this section on a fair and
Req. No. 17242 Page 1

1 reas onable basis in compliance with paragraph 10 of subsection C of
2 Section 85.5 of this title in an amount not to exceed Seventy-five
3 Thousand Dollars ($75,000.00). The Department is hereby authorized
4 to may charge registration and exhibit space fees necessary to cover
5 the costs of the conference and shall deposit the fees plus any
6 other conference proceeds, including donated funds, into an agency
7 special account to be created by the Special Agency Account Board.
8 Expenditure of monies from the agency special account shall be for
9 purposes incidental to the tourism and recreation industry
10 conference, and shall be approved by the Commission Executive
11 Director.
12 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
